name: Surprise Barbecue Hot Dogs
author: Shane Arthur Pyle
summary: A family favorite for years. My mother learned this baked hot dog recipe in the Girl Scouts in the 1950's.
ingredients: ½ (8 ounce) package processed cheese food (such as Velveeta®), cubed, or to taste
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat
Stir in onion and brown sugar and cook until onion is soft but not yet brown, about 5 minutes
Add ketchup, mustard, and Worcestershire sauce; bring to a simmer
Cut a slit through each hot dog and fill with cubes of cheese food
Place dogs in buns and cover meat with onion sauce, about 3 tablespoons each
Bake in the preheated oven until piping hot throughout, about 15 minutes
